1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,950
The operator told me the GPS failed under a tunnel.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,949
Black Box checked the recording and said: that story is wrong.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,449
Robotics teams collect hours of video, lidar, telemetry,

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:18,949
and controller logs.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,949
The evidence exists, but forensic review is still manual.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,449
One real driving session. No labels.

7
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:35,950
Just the operator's note: check the tunnel.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,950
Black Box opens it as a forensic case.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,950
Not a one-shot summary.

10
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,950
Opus 4.7 runs as a managed forensic agent —

11
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,950
reading files, calling tools, streaming events.

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:54,950
Memory carries forward across runs.

13
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,950
It doesn't send every frame.

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:02,950
Telemetry selects suspicious windows.

15
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,950
High-resolution visual mining checks the relevant cameras.

16
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,950
The tunnel did mildly degrade GNSS.

17
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,450
But the RTK heading failure was already present

18
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:20,950
43 minutes earlier.

19
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,950
Drive-by-wire was never engaged.

20
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,950
The tunnel could not have caused this.

21
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,950
Operator hypothesis: refuted.

22
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,450
The real failure is lower level.

23
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,950
Moving-base antenna: healthy.

24
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,950
Rover: never receives valid RTK heading.

25
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:54,950
The correction path was broken before the car left the lot.

26
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,950
The output isn't just a report.

27
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,450
Scoped patch: RTCM IDs, UART link check,

28
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:06,950
and a human-review gate.

29
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,949
Black Box proposes. Engineer approves.

30
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,449
Same benchmark slice. Opus 4.6 vs 4.7.

31
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,449
Same cases, same prompts, same budget.

32
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,949
On simple post-mortems they tie.

33
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,449
But robot forensics punishes confident wrong answers.

34
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:26,949
4.6 committed on every under-specified case.

35
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,949
4.7 abstained every time.

36
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,949
Not a single-car demo.

37
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,949
More car sessions. A robotic boat case.

38
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,949
Clean recordings and injected benchmark failures.

39
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,949
When evidence is weak, it refuses to invent a bug.

40
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,949
No evidence. No claim.

41
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,949
Open benchmark. Reproducible runs.

42
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,949
Robot forensics in minutes, for cents.
